==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Od
<hw>Od</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G., fr. Gr. <?/
passage.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An alleged force or natural
power, supposed, by <persfn>Reichenbach</persfn> and others, to produce
the phenomena of mesmerism, and to be developed by various agencies, as
by magnets, heat, light, chemical or vital action, etc.; -- called also
<altname>odyle</altname> or the <altname>odylic force</altname>.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>od</qex> force of German Reichenbach⟦br⟧
Which still, from female finger tips, burnt blue.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Odal</ent>⟦br⟧
